lenders.name: Kimberly Anne Hoffman
lenders.occupational_info: Kimberly Anne Hoffman is dedicated to helping others. Her ultimate goal lies in empowering patients to heal themselves. Kimberly Anne obtained her California State Acupuncture license and is certified in both Acupuncture and Chinese Herbal Medicine. She earned her Masters Degree in Traditional Chinese Medicine from the American College of Traditional Chinese Medicine and has worked in both clinical and hospital settings including the Haight Ashbury Free Clinic, California Pacific Medical Center in the Stroke Department, The Jewish Home for the Aged in Hospice Care, The Auricular Community Clinic and the ACTCM Community Clinic. After attending Zhejiang Medical University in Hangzhou, China, she completed an advanced clinical internship. As a student of Mary Elizabeth Wakefield, she has also been certified in Facial Rejuvenation. In addition to Chinese Medicine, Kimberly Anne studied the healing modalities of Reiki and Chinese Face Reading, where she is completing the practitioner’s training course with Jean Haner. From Jean she has also learned and practices personal energy clearing and space clearing. Her focuses include but are not limited to: 1. Food Intolerances and Environmental Toxins 2. Psycho/Spritual/Emotional Issues – Stress, Depression, Anxiety, Addictions 3. Hormonal Balancing – peri-menopause, menopause, acupuncture face lifts (facial rejuvenation), fertility, weight loss 4. Pain Management – general pain, sciatica, headaches, sports injuries .
